cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CE, cs.ED, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper is primarily focused on machine learning and its democratization through an educational approach. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the use of graphical user interfaces to convey programming skills to an applied-science target group, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a web application that dynamically translates GUI interactions into valid source code for the Python machine learning framework PHOTON, which can be considered as a computational engineering solution. 
- cs.ED (Computer Science and Education): The paper proposes an educational approach to teach programming skills to an applied-science target group, which falls under the domain of computer science and education. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a proof-of-concept, open-source web application, which can be considered as a software engineering solution.
